ity\": 0.85,\n            \"pathway_coherence\": 0.86,\n            \"environmental_progression\": 0.88,\n            \"target_achievement\": 0.90,\n            \"overall_confidence\": 0.87,\n            \"feedback\": \"Dual C1 fixation (formate and formaldehyde) feeding into the formose-cyanosulfidic route. Nicely demonstrates how multiple hydrothermal C1 products converge on surface chemistry. The formate production (rxn_001) on greigite is well-established, and the formose-to-cyanosulfidic sequence is the core strength of this network.\",\n            \"approved\": true,\n            \"problematic_reactions\": [\"rxn_002\"],\n            \"suggestions\": [\"Add a formate-to-formaldehyde reduction step to better connect the two C1 fixation products\"]\n        },\n        {\n            \"pathway_id\": \"P10\",\n            \"reaction_scores\": {\n                \"rxn_008\": 0.90,\n                \"rxn_010\": 0.82,\n                \"rxn_009\": 0.85\n            },\n            \"chemical_feasibility\": 0.85,\n            \"pathway_coherence\": 0.83,\n            \"environmental_progression\": 0.80,\n            \"target_achievement\": 0.88,\n            \"overall_confidence\": 0.84,\n            \"feedback\": \"Shows the convergent dual-environment production of threonine with ammonia recycling between nitrile hydrolysis (which releases NH3) and reductive amination (which consumes NH3). This is an elegant network feature that demonstrates self-sustaining nitrogen cycling. Both threonine-producing reactions are literature-supported.\",\n            \"approved\": true,\n            \"problematic_reactions\": [],\n            \"suggestions\": [\"Explicitly quantify ammonia fluxes to demonstrate recycling feasibility\"]\n        }\n    ],\n    \"best_pathway_id\": \"P7\",\n    \"overall_confidence\": 0.85,\n    \"network_feedback\": \"This is a well-constructed synthesis network for L-threonine that faithfully incorporates both major literature-supported prebiotic 